    <p>
        1. The site needs to look good, if the design of the website is not simple and user friendly then people will not use your site or they will have a lot of questions about it. <br />
2. The site must be hosted somewhere so it is accessible from any web browser (assuming its a public website). <br />
3. The site needs to have 508 compliance so blind people can use your site. <br />
4. The site needs to be fast so users do not have to wait to use it. <br />
5. The site may need to have authorization and log in pages so people can access their data <br />
6. A good website is optimized and does not do unnecessary things such as accessing the database in excess. <br />
7. A good website does not show sensitive information in the URL by using POST. <br />
8. Good websites use error handling so if the website breaks then there is information about the issue. <br />
9. Good websites use data validation for user inputs to make sure data is consistent and correct. <br />
10. Good websites have eye contrast between the foreground and background. <br />
11. Websites should be intuitive so users can navigate it easily. <br />
12. The content of a website should be accurate and reliable, and if necessary should say where the information came from. <br />
13. A good website uses photos and visuals to intrigue the user. <br />
14. A good website takes advantage of using ads but not in an obnoxious way. <br />
15. Good websites may be accessible on mobile phones as well. <br />
16. The site should have a useful help/support area. <br />
17. A site should not have unexpected popups or requests. <br />
18. A websites content should be checked for grammar and spelling issues. <br />
19. A good website for a company will link to their social media accounts. <br />
    20. Some good websites have review and discussion sections.  <br />

